WEBVTT

00:26.834 --> 00:28.875
IS IT OVER?

00:28.875 --> 00:32.834
UH, YEAH,
2 HOURS AND 45
MINUTES LATER.

00:32.834 --> 00:34.458
I KNOW.
IT'S THE DIRECTOR'S CUT.
IT'S WAY TOO LONG.

00:34.458 --> 00:35.792
IT'S--IT--

00:36.834 --> 00:38.083
ARE YOU CRYING?

00:38.083 --> 00:39.458
NO.

00:39.458 --> 00:41.000
'CAUSE IT LOOKS LIKE
YOU MIGHT HAVE BEEN--

00:41.000 --> 00:44.708
OK, THERE MAY HAVE BEEN
A TEAR SHED OR SOMETHING.
I DON'T REMEMBER.

00:44.708 --> 00:45.959
YOU WERE CRYING.

00:45.959 --> 00:47.583
THAT'S A GOOD THING,
RIGHT?

00:47.583 --> 00:49.208
NOT UNLESS I WAS
BORED TO TEARS.

00:50.166 --> 00:50.250
SEE, THAT'S JUST MEAN.

00:52.208 --> 00:54.083
I KNOW. I'M SORRY.

00:54.083 --> 00:55.333
NOTHING BRINGS OUT
THE INNER BULLY IN ME

00:55.333 --> 00:57.333
QUITE LIKE THE SIGHT
OF A NERVOUS FILMMAKER.

01:00.834 --> 01:02.041
[LAUGHS]

01:02.041 --> 01:02.250
WELL?

01:04.208 --> 01:04.834
IT'S GOOD.

01:04.834 --> 01:07.625
IT'S REALLY GOOD.

01:07.625 --> 01:08.834
YOU THINK?
YEAH, I MEAN,

01:08.834 --> 01:12.667
I CAN SEE SOMETHING
ACTUALLY HAPPENING
WITH THIS.

01:12.667 --> 01:13.667
REALLY?

01:13.667 --> 01:15.375
YEAH.

01:15.375 --> 01:17.000
THAT'S WHY
I WAS CRYING.

01:17.000 --> 01:19.917
IT'S A PRETTY
AMAZING THING

01:19.917 --> 01:22.041
TO BE THERE
FOR THE MOMENT
YOUR BEST FRIEND

01:22.041 --> 01:25.083
BECOMES EXACTLY
WHAT HE'S DREAMT ABOUT
HIS ENTIRE LIFE.

01:27.583 --> 01:30.291
AND YOU KNOW WHAT
WAS REALLY SURPRISING?

01:30.291 --> 01:32.834
WHAT?
CHARLIE.

01:32.834 --> 01:33.583
WHAT ABOUT HIM?

01:33.583 --> 01:35.875
HE WAS...
SHOCKINGLY GOOD.

01:35.875 --> 01:37.291
I KNOW. IT KILLS ME!

01:37.291 --> 01:40.083
IN REAL LIFE, THE GUY
BARELY PASSES FOR HUMAN,

01:40.083 --> 01:41.917
BUT ON-SCREEN
HE'S GOT SOMETHING.

01:41.917 --> 01:43.250
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS,
BUT IT WORKS.

01:43.250 --> 01:45.166
HE'S NOT THAT BAD
OF A GUY, DAWSON.

01:45.166 --> 01:48.291
I KNOW HE WAS
A JERK TO JEN,

01:48.291 --> 01:50.875
BUT I THINK THAT WAS
MORE OUT OF FEAR
THAN ANYTHING ELSE.

01:50.875 --> 01:53.208
UNDERNEATH THE HAIR
AND THE ATTITUDE,

01:53.208 --> 01:54.959
I THINK HE--

01:56.583 --> 01:58.291
HOLY SMOKES, LEERY.

01:58.291 --> 02:00.083
YOU WORK FAST,
DON'T YA?

02:00.083 --> 02:01.625
BREAK UP WITH BETTY,
AND YOU ALREADY GOT
VERONICA IN YOUR BED.

02:01.625 --> 02:03.750
HEY!

02:03.750 --> 02:05.834
HOW'D YOU LIKE THE MOVIE?
DID SHE LIKE THE MOVIE?

02:05.834 --> 02:07.708
IF YOU WOULD
LET ME RESPOND,
I COULD TELL YOU.

02:08.625 --> 02:10.000
I THOUGHT
IT WAS EXCELLENT.

02:10.000 --> 02:12.500
YEAH. YEAH, I KNOW.

02:12.500 --> 02:14.959
BUT WAS THERE
EVER ANY DOUBT?

02:14.959 --> 02:16.792
BUT THIS IS
GOOD NEWS, HUH?

02:16.792 --> 02:19.125
BECAUSE IT'S HIGH TIME
WE SCREEN THIS PUPPY.

02:19.125 --> 02:21.000
YEAH, WE STILL
GOT A LOTTA WORK
TO DO.

02:21.000 --> 02:22.125
WELL, THEN YOU BETTER
GET TO WORK, CHIEF.

02:22.125 --> 02:24.834
TOMORROW'S APPROACHING
AWFULLY FAST!

02:24.834 --> 02:26.375
EXCUSE ME?

02:26.375 --> 02:28.000
OOH...

02:28.000 --> 02:29.041
I FORGOT TO TELL YOU,
DIDN'T I?

02:29.041 --> 02:31.834
SILLY ME.
SILLY WHAT?

02:31.834 --> 02:34.041
WE'RE SCREENING
THE MOVIE TOMORROW
AT SCHOOL

02:34.041 --> 02:36.875
FOR CAST,
CREW, AND ASSORTED
HIGHBROW INTELLECTUALS.

02:36.875 --> 02:37.834
NO, WE'RE NOT.

02:37.834 --> 02:41.083
SEE...I KNEW YOU'D
HAVE THAT REACTION.

02:41.083 --> 02:42.291
THAT'S WHY
I WENT AROUND YOU.

02:44.667 --> 02:45.708
THE TRAIN HAS LEFT
THE STATION.

02:45.708 --> 02:48.375
EXCUSE ME.

02:48.375 --> 02:49.959
OLIVER, HOLD ON!

04:03.875 --> 04:06.208
SERIOUSLY, NOT ONLY
IS THIS THE BEST MOVIE

04:06.208 --> 04:07.333
I'VE EVER BEEN
ASSOCIATED WITH,

04:07.333 --> 04:11.250
BUT THIS JUST MIGHT BE
THE BEST MOVIE EVER.

04:11.250 --> 04:13.208
ARE YOU JOKING?

04:13.208 --> 04:15.083
IT'S--
IT'S WAY TOO LONG,

04:15.083 --> 04:17.541
IT'S LIKE
THE ENGLISH PATIENT
WITHOUT THE LAUGHS.

04:17.541 --> 04:19.291
DAWSON, YOU'RE
BEING WAY TOO HARD
ON YOURSELF HERE.

04:19.291 --> 04:22.000
I MEAN,
I'M THE WRITER.

04:22.000 --> 04:24.417
I'M THE ONE
WHO'S SUPPOSED TO
LOATHE MY OWN WORK,

04:24.417 --> 04:25.667
BUT I DON'T.

04:25.667 --> 04:27.083
ACTUALLY, I THINK
IT KICKS SOME SERIOUS
DONKEY ASS.

04:27.083 --> 04:28.583
I'M NOT SAYING IT--

04:30.333 --> 04:32.417
NEVER MIND. I'M NOT
SAYING IT'S TERRIBLE.

04:32.417 --> 04:35.208
I'M SAYING IT NEEDS
A HELL OF A LOT OF WORK.

04:35.208 --> 04:36.750
ENTIRE SCENES
NEED TO BE RESHOT.

04:36.750 --> 04:37.542
WHICH ONES?

04:37.542 --> 04:40.083
THE SEX SCENE, FOR ONE.
WHY?

04:40.083 --> 04:41.583
FROM A CERTAIN ANGLE,

04:41.583 --> 04:44.500
YOU CAN ACTUALLY SEE CHARLIE
IN ALL OF HIS...GLORY.

04:44.500 --> 04:46.083
YOU DON'T SAY.

04:46.083 --> 04:47.417
IS IT SUBSTANTIAL?

04:47.417 --> 04:48.750
IT'S ENOUGH TO WARRANT
ITS OWN CREDIT
IN THE MAIN TITLES.

04:48.750 --> 04:52.583
WHEN THE FILM'S
INEVITABLY ACQUIRED
BY A MAJOR STUDIO,

04:52.583 --> 04:55.959
WE'LL HAVE THE CASH
TO CGI IT OUT OF THERE.

04:55.959 --> 04:57.125
NEXT?

04:57.125 --> 04:59.333
I FEEL LIKE I'M WORKING
WITH GILBERT GODFREY.

04:59.333 --> 05:01.959
THIS IS...I...

05:01.959 --> 05:03.708
YOU KNOW WHAT THE REAL
PROBLEM IS, RIGHT?

05:03.708 --> 05:04.583
[LAUGHS]

05:07.125 --> 05:08.542
PLEASE, ENLIGHTEN ME.

05:08.542 --> 05:11.875
YOU'RE STILL REELING
FROM YOUR BREAKUP
WITH JEN.

05:11.875 --> 05:13.750
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S IT, OLIVER.

05:13.750 --> 05:14.875
COME ON, CAPTAIN.

05:14.875 --> 05:16.458
YOU DATED HER
FOR MONTHS.

05:16.458 --> 05:17.959
SHE HELPED YOU
GRIEVE.

05:17.959 --> 05:21.125
SHE ROBBED YOU
OF YOUR PRECIOUS
FLOWER, RIGHT?

05:21.125 --> 05:24.583
I MEAN, I DON'T CARE
HOW COOL YOU WANNA
PLAY THAT OFF,

05:24.583 --> 05:26.917
BUT THAT MEANS
SOMETHING, BUCKO,
SERIOUSLY.

05:26.917 --> 05:28.542
DO YOU WANNA TALK
ABOUT IT?

05:28.542 --> 05:29.917
NO.

05:29.917 --> 05:32.041
GREAT.

05:32.041 --> 05:33.083
CAN I ASK YOU
ANOTHER QUESTION?

05:33.458 --> 05:33.917
SURE.

05:33.917 --> 05:35.834
WELL...

05:35.834 --> 05:39.708
WOULD IT
BE A PROBLEM
IF I WERE TO, SAY,

05:39.708 --> 05:41.208
ASK HER OUT?

05:46.834 --> 05:49.417
Pacey [panting]:
WHERE...ON EARTH...

05:49.417 --> 05:51.708
DID YOU LEARN
HOW TO DO THAT?

05:51.708 --> 05:53.583
NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC.

05:53.583 --> 05:55.667
[BOTH LAUGH]

05:55.667 --> 05:58.500
BUT MOST GUYS
LOSE CONSCIOUSNESS
SOMEWHERE IN THE MIDDLE.

05:58.500 --> 06:01.333
HOW MANY GUYS
HAVE YOU DONE THAT WITH?

06:01.333 --> 06:03.792
ENOUGH TO KNOW YOU'VE
GOT STAYING POWER.

06:03.792 --> 06:05.417
[GRUNTS]

06:11.000 --> 06:12.583
[CHUCKLES]

06:13.125 --> 06:15.667
I'M REALLY GLAD

06:15.667 --> 06:18.667
THAT BRECHER DECIDED
TO TAKE HIS WIFE
TO THE CARIBBEAN,

06:18.667 --> 06:19.917
AND I AM REALLY GLAD

06:19.917 --> 06:22.708
THAT THEY ASKED YOU
TO STAY HERE
WHILE THEY'RE GONE.

06:22.708 --> 06:23.708
I'M AS GLAD AS YOU ARE.

06:23.708 --> 06:28.583
I AM MORE GLAD.
I AM GLADDER. GLADDEST.

06:28.583 --> 06:31.041
AND I CAN'T FEEL ANYTHING
BELOW MY WAIST.

06:31.041 --> 06:32.291
IS THAT SUPPOSED
TO HAPPEN?

06:32.291 --> 06:34.417
GIVE ME ANOTHER HOUR,
YOU'LL BE IN A COMA.

06:37.458 --> 06:38.375
HOW MANY IS ENOUGH?

06:38.375 --> 06:40.583
WHAT YOU TALKIN'
'BOUT, WILLIS?

06:40.583 --> 06:42.583
OH, YOU KNOW,
IT'S NOTHING,

06:42.583 --> 06:45.000
JUST--AHEM--
HOW MANY...GUYS...

06:46.959 --> 06:49.000
IS ENOUGH TO...

06:49.000 --> 06:51.750
HAVE I GIVEN ACCESS
TO MY MOST INTIMATE
OF AREAS?

06:51.750 --> 06:53.542
WELL, YEAH.
RESPECTFULLY, OF COURSE.

06:53.542 --> 06:57.000
YOU'RE REALLY
ASKING ME THIS QUESTION?

06:57.000 --> 06:59.083
NO, BECAUSE
IT'S NONE OF MY BUSINESS.

06:59.083 --> 07:02.458
FORGET I ASKED.

07:02.458 --> 07:03.458
MM...

07:03.458 --> 07:05.917
HOW MANY GIRLS
HAVE YOU--

07:05.917 --> 07:07.792
6.

07:07.792 --> 07:09.834
7 INCLUDING YOU.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.250
DIDN'T TAKE YOU LONG
TO THINK OF THAT ONE.

07:14.250 --> 07:16.458
NOPE. HA HA.

07:17.417 --> 07:20.834
THAT'S NOT...A LOT.

07:21.875 --> 07:24.417
THAT'S NOT A LOT
COMPARED TO WHAT?

07:24.417 --> 07:27.625
COMPARED
TO OTHER PEOPLE.

07:27.625 --> 07:29.125
OTHER PEOPLE LIKE YOU?

07:29.125 --> 07:30.917
YOU TOTALLY ARE ASKING
ME THAT QUESTION!

07:30.917 --> 07:32.083
I TOLD YOU MINE.

07:32.083 --> 07:33.166
YOU DON'T WANNA KNOW

07:33.166 --> 07:36.250
HOW MANY MEN I'VE SLEPT
WITH, PACEY. TRUST ME.

07:36.250 --> 07:39.083
YOU THINK YOU DO RIGHT NOW,
BUT ONCE I'VE TOLD YOU,

07:39.083 --> 07:40.792
YOU'D WISH I HADN'T.
IT'S THAT MANY?

07:40.792 --> 07:42.083
[LAUGHS]

07:42.083 --> 07:43.542
LET'S PUT IT THIS WAY.

07:43.542 --> 07:46.291
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD
OF EMMANUELLE,
LADY CHATTERLEY,

07:46.291 --> 07:47.291
MADONNA?

07:47.291 --> 07:48.291
OH, YEAH.

07:48.291 --> 07:50.166
PRUDES.

08:01.458 --> 08:01.917
HEY.

08:01.917 --> 08:03.667
OH, HI.

08:06.333 --> 08:07.000
WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:07.000 --> 08:09.375
NOTHING.

08:09.375 --> 08:11.417
THAT'S NOT TRUE,
ACTUALLY. UH...

08:11.417 --> 08:14.542
WHAT'S GOING ON?
I'M, UH...

08:14.542 --> 08:16.625
I'M NERVOUS ABOUT
THE SCREENING TODAY.

08:16.625 --> 08:19.667
THE MOVIE'S NOT--
IT'S NOT FINISHED.

08:19.667 --> 08:21.125
BUT FROM THE
OUTSIDE PERSPECTIVE,

08:21.125 --> 08:22.333
IT LOOKS LIKE
IT'S FINISHED.

08:22.333 --> 08:23.792
BUT IT'S--
REALLY, IT--

08:25.083 --> 08:26.333
IT'S NOT...FINISHED.

08:26.333 --> 08:27.250
WHY ARE YOU SMILING?

08:27.250 --> 08:29.667
IT'S OK
IF THIS IS WEIRD.

08:29.667 --> 08:31.458
WHICH THING?

08:31.458 --> 08:33.833
YOU AND ME.

08:33.833 --> 08:36.542
AH. [LAUGHS]

08:36.542 --> 08:37.582
I THINK IT'S OK

08:37.582 --> 08:40.125
IF WE DON'T KNOW HOW
TO DO THIS NEXT PART.

08:40.125 --> 08:41.332
I THINK IT'D BE ODD
IF WE DID, RIGHT?

08:41.332 --> 08:44.125
RIGHT. RIGHT,
IT'S JUST--

08:45.500 --> 08:46.792
NO.

08:46.792 --> 08:48.625
WHAT?

08:48.625 --> 08:49.750
NO, IT JUST--

08:52.333 --> 08:54.250
THIS IS SUCH A FAMILIAR
SCENE, YOU KNOW?

08:54.250 --> 08:57.333
YOU AND ME IN HERE
JUST KIND OF CHECKING IN
WITH EACH OTHER

08:57.333 --> 09:00.000
BEFORE WE GO OUT
INTO THE WORLD...

09:00.000 --> 09:01.875
IT WAS SUCH A COMFORT.

09:01.875 --> 09:02.875
FOR ME, TOO.

09:02.875 --> 09:05.875
I DON'T THINK
THAT HAS TO STOP.

09:05.875 --> 09:07.542
I HOPE NOT.

09:07.542 --> 09:08.959
RIGHT, BUT...

09:08.959 --> 09:10.959
LAST WEEK YOU WERE
UP AGAINST THE COUNTER

09:10.959 --> 09:13.208
AND I WAS COVERING
YOUR FACE WITH KISSES,

09:13.208 --> 09:15.208
AND NOW...
WE CAN'T DO THAT.

09:15.208 --> 09:17.166
I MEAN, IT'S--
THAT'S DONE.

09:22.792 --> 09:26.250
WHO'S TO SAY
WHAT WE CAN
AND CAN'T DO?

09:30.625 --> 09:32.208
YOU SAW THE MOVIE?

09:32.208 --> 09:33.417
MM-HMM. I SAID THAT,
DIDN'T I?

09:33.417 --> 09:34.542
DIDN'T I
JUST SAY THAT?

09:34.542 --> 09:35.875
I WANT YOU TO BE
HONEST WITH ME, JOEY.

09:35.875 --> 09:37.500
FRIENDS ARE HONEST,
AND THAT'S WHAT
YOU'VE GOT TO BE:

09:37.500 --> 09:39.250
HONEST AND UNMERCIFUL.
HOW BRILLIANT WAS I?

09:39.250 --> 09:40.708
YOU WERE HORRIBLE.
GIVE IT TO ME STRAIGHT.

09:40.708 --> 09:41.917
I CAN HANDLE IT.
NO. YOU'RE WASHED UP.

09:41.917 --> 09:43.208
YOU'RE NO GOOD.
STOP SUGARCOATING!

09:43.208 --> 09:44.041
WHAT IS THE BOTTOM LINE?

09:44.041 --> 09:46.125
AUDREY,
YOU WERE FANTASTIC!

09:46.125 --> 09:49.708
YOU'RE CHARMING AND
FUNNY AND BEAUTIFUL
AND SEXY,

09:49.708 --> 09:51.667
AND YOU HAVE
AMAZING CHEMISTRY
WITH CHARLIE,

09:51.667 --> 09:54.750
WHO, SURPRISINGLY,
IS REALLY GOOD.

09:54.750 --> 09:57.542
CHARLIE? WHY ARE WE TALKING
ABOUT CHARLIE HERE?

09:57.542 --> 09:58.792
THIS IS ABOUT ME:
MY PERFORMANCE,

09:58.792 --> 10:01.083
MY APPEARANCE,
MY FUTURE CAREER.

10:01.083 --> 10:03.917
I'M A NEUROTIC ACTRESS,
FOR CRYING OUT LOUD.
HAVE SOME SENSITIVITY.

10:03.917 --> 10:05.291
AUDREY, YOU'RE
GONNA SEE THE MOVIE
IN LESS THAN 3 HOURS.

10:05.291 --> 10:06.625
STOP INTERROGATING ME.

10:06.625 --> 10:10.708
YOU LOOK HOT.
WHY DO YOU LOOK HOT?

10:11.583 --> 10:14.792
WELL, I DON'T KNOW.
I JUST--

10:14.792 --> 10:15.750
WAIT. DO I LOOK HOT?
IN THE MOVIE, I MEAN.

10:15.750 --> 10:17.750
DO I LOOK HOT
OR DO I LOOK SCORCHING?

10:17.750 --> 10:19.959
WHAT SCENE DO I LOOK BEST IN?
IS IT THE END?

10:19.959 --> 10:21.083
I BET IT'S THE END,
ISN'T IT?

10:21.083 --> 10:21.708
AUDREY.

10:21.708 --> 10:25.250
SORRY. SORRY. [SIGHS]

10:25.250 --> 10:28.500
CAN I ASK YOU
ONE MORE QUESTION?
IT'S NOT ABOUT THE MOVIE.

10:28.500 --> 10:29.458
WELL, IF IT'S ABOUT YOU,
I GOT NOTHIN' LEFT.

10:29.458 --> 10:31.959
NO. IT'S ABOUT PACEY.

10:31.959 --> 10:34.583
THIS MORNING,
WE WERE TALKING,

10:34.583 --> 10:37.291
AND HE ASKED ME
HOW MANY GUYS I'D SLEPT WITH.

10:37.291 --> 10:39.500
HE DID?
YEAH. WELL...

10:39.500 --> 10:41.166
SORT OF. I DON'T KNOW.
IT CAME UP.

10:41.166 --> 10:43.625
DID YOU TELL HIM?
NO! NO! NOT YET!

10:43.625 --> 10:45.291
I'M DEBATING IT.
WHAT DO YOU THINK
I SHOULD DO?

10:45.291 --> 10:46.625
I DON'T KNOW.

10:46.625 --> 10:49.291
WELL, WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

10:49.291 --> 10:51.417
WELL, I HAVE TO SAY
THAT HONESTY HAS
ALWAYS WORKED FOR ME.

10:51.417 --> 10:53.625
I SHOULD TELL HIM.

10:53.625 --> 10:55.625
HMM, BUT THEN AGAIN,
THE MALE EGO

10:55.625 --> 10:57.125
IS A VERY FRAGILE
AND DELICATE THING,

10:57.125 --> 10:59.041
AND IF HE'S ASKING YOU
THE QUESTION,

10:59.041 --> 11:01.458
IT'S PROBABLY
BECAUSE HE'S HARBORING
SOME DEEP INSECURITIES,

11:01.458 --> 11:02.458
IN WHICH CASE,
THE ANSWER WOULD DO
MORE HARM THAN GOOD.

11:02.458 --> 11:04.458
I SHOULDN'T TELL HIM.

11:04.458 --> 11:06.000
IT DEPENDS.
ON WHAT?

11:06.000 --> 11:07.792
ON HOW MANY GUYS
YOU'VE SLEPT WITH.

11:15.041 --> 11:17.834
USUALLY, I DON'T LIKE
TO WATCH THE WORK
THAT I'VE DONE.

11:17.834 --> 11:19.500
I FEEL LIKE IT INTERFERES
WITH MY PROCESS,

11:19.500 --> 11:22.625
BUT I'M WILLING TO MAKE
AN EXCEPTION FOR DAWSON.
YOU KNOW, HE'S MY FRIEND.

11:22.625 --> 11:24.000
WELL, THAT'S
GENEROUS OF YOU.

11:24.000 --> 11:25.375
OK. I STILL
DIDN'T UNDERSTAND

11:25.375 --> 11:26.542
WHY JOEY
GOT DROPPED OFF FRONT,

11:26.542 --> 11:29.208
BUT I HAVE TO SEARCH FOR
A PARKING SPACE WITH YOU.

11:29.208 --> 11:31.333
IT'S ALL PART
OF THE DEAL.
[LAUGHS]

11:31.333 --> 11:32.375
AND WHAT DEAL
WOULD THAT BE?

11:32.375 --> 11:35.792
YOU KNOW,
OUR ARRANGEMENT
WE GOT GOIN'.

11:35.792 --> 11:39.291
AND WHAT ARRANGEMENT
WOULD THAT BE?

11:39.291 --> 11:41.583
WELL, I MEAN,
I UNDERSTAND

11:41.583 --> 11:42.959
WHERE THERE'S
NO CLEAR DEFINITIONS

11:42.959 --> 11:44.166
TO THE ARRANGEMENT
THAT WE HAVE,

11:44.166 --> 11:45.834
BUT I WAS THINKING,
ACTUALLY, THAT WE--

11:45.834 --> 11:47.291
YOU KNOW,
WE MIGHT WANT TO
GET INTO THAT POINT

11:47.291 --> 11:49.208
WHERE WE
START DEFINING
HOW IT IS THAT--

11:49.208 --> 11:51.667
GOD, MAN,
MY PALMS ARE SWEATY.
WHY IS THAT?

11:51.667 --> 11:53.625
27.
WHOO! WHAT?

11:53.625 --> 11:54.250
27 MEN.

11:54.250 --> 11:56.208
WHAT?!

11:56.208 --> 11:58.250
STOP, PLEASE!

12:04.250 --> 12:07.625
JACK, HURRY UP!
I DON'T WANT TO BE LATE.

12:09.208 --> 12:10.291
HI.

12:10.291 --> 12:12.208
HELLO.

12:13.375 --> 12:15.375
CAN I HELP YOU?

12:15.375 --> 12:17.750
JENNIFER. JEN.

12:17.750 --> 12:19.125
YEAH.

12:19.125 --> 12:20.792
I'M CLIFTON.

12:21.834 --> 12:23.375
CLIFTON?

12:23.375 --> 12:25.542
YOUR GRANDMOTHER TOLD ME
YOU WERE VERY BEAUTIFUL,

12:25.542 --> 12:28.792
BUT I GUESS WORDS
CAN'T QUITE CONVEY
A THING LIKE THAT.

12:32.041 --> 12:33.417
THIS IS CLIFTON.

12:34.959 --> 12:36.750
DAWSON.
NO.

12:36.750 --> 12:37.959
IT'S JACK, ACTUALLY.

12:37.959 --> 12:39.834
JACK. THE HOMOSEXUAL!

12:39.834 --> 12:42.250
NICE TO MEET YOU.

12:42.250 --> 12:43.917
YOU, TOO.

12:43.917 --> 12:44.959
I'M A FRIEND OF EVELYN'S.

12:44.959 --> 12:47.417
SHE INVITED ME
TO JOIN YOU ALL THIS EVENING

12:47.417 --> 12:49.792
FOR THE SCREENING
OF DAWSON LEERY'S FILM.

12:49.792 --> 12:51.333
NICE.

12:51.333 --> 12:54.125
AH, MR. SMALLS.

12:54.125 --> 12:57.208
